Curry's bat (Glauconycteris curryae) is a species of vesper bat in the family Vespertilionidae.
It is found in Cameroon and Democratic Republic of the Congo.
Its natural habitats are subtropical or tropical moist lowland forests and subtropical or tropical swamps.
The specific name was originally curryi, but it was emended to be curryae in accordance with ยง31.1.2 of the ICZN Code.